do I choose an SEO consultant for my SaaS startup in Australia?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Look for someone who understands SaaS buying behaviour specifically — not just general SEO. They should be able to speak to funnel-stage keyword strategy, high-intent page types like alternatives, comparisons, and use cases, and how organic search connects to pipeline metrics. Ask about their experience with Australian market targeting and whether they have worked with companies at your stage.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Can a SaaS SEO consultant help with both Australia and Europe targeting?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Pages can be structured by region, language, and intent without creating duplicate-content problems. For companies targeting both ANZ and European markets, this requires deliberate site architecture and hreflang setup, not just translating copy and hoping Google figures it out.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Do SaaS companies need to blog constantly to rank?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Not constantly — strategically. High-intent pages like alternatives, comparisons, and use cases plus a focused blog cluster consistently outperforms weekly blogs published for the sake of it. Content volume without intent alignment just creates noise that Google has to crawl and users ignore.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Does Mitch Chadban work with dev teams on technical SEO?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Technical SEO recommendations come with clear implementation briefs — not vague advice that gets deprioritised in the sprint. Working alongside designers, devs, founders, and marketing teams is a standard part of the process.\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script>";
